1
00:00:02,366 --> 00:00:07,166
Pitter-patter…

2
00:00:07,166 --> 00:00:12,833
Outside, the drizzling sound of rain weaves the most perfect white noise, turning the rustling of book pages and the clicking of a mouse indoors into something no longer dull and monotonous.

3
00:00:12,833 --> 00:00:17,633
Such a lazy moment is just right for leisurely passing time at home, soaking in the aroma of coffee together with Lucien.

4
00:00:17,633 --> 00:00:20,433
MC: Pfft…

5
00:00:20,433 --> 00:00:25,733
Lucien: Did you see something funny? What’s got you laughing so much?

6
00:00:25,733 --> 00:00:29,666
Hearing my voice, Lucien lifts his head curiously from the other side of the sofa.

7
00:00:29,666 --> 00:00:33,633
I beckon with a smile, tugging his sleeve as I bring him over to my computer.

8
00:00:33,633 --> 00:00:37,333
MC: Take a look at my new desktop pet companion~

9
00:00:37,333 --> 00:00:41,866
On the computer desktop, a little bunny hops around in response to my mouse clicks.

10
00:00:41,866 --> 00:00:47,800
MC: Look, her name is Nobi. Once the system's set up, she chats with me whenever I poke her.

11
00:00:47,800 --> 00:00:51,766
As I speak, I poke her twice. The little bunny blinks, and with a pop, a dialogue box jumps out above her head.

12
00:00:51,766 --> 00:00:56,033
Nobi: "Want to ask the world’s cutest Nobi Rabbit something?"

13
00:00:56,033 --> 00:01:01,766
Nobi: "Feeling wronged? Listen to me, it’s better to trouble others than to wrong yourself!"

14
00:01:01,766 --> 00:01:04,633
MC: Haha, isn’t it funny?

15
00:01:04,633 --> 00:01:10,133
Lucien: Mm, she’s certainly a little bunny even livelier than MC.

16
00:01:10,133 --> 00:01:14,266
Lucien’s gaze falls on the Nobi pin on my collar.

17
00:01:14,266 --> 00:01:22,566
Lucien: Speaking of which, you really have bought a lot of Nobi Rabbit merchandise lately… Do you like her a lot?

18
00:01:22,566 --> 00:01:27,000
MC: Of course I do! But this is only one of the reasons; the more important reason is this!

19
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:32,100
With a cheerful lilt in my voice, I click open a video.

20
00:01:32,100 --> 00:01:36,333
MC: Behold—"The Bunny Arrives!"

21
00:01:36,333 --> 00:01:41,200
In the video, an excited couple waves at the camera, and perched on their shoulders is none other than... Nobi Rabbit!

22
00:01:41,200 --> 00:01:46,433
With his index finger hooked under his chin, Lucien watches the interaction between Nobi and the couple in the video thoughtfully and slightly raises an eyebrow.

23
00:01:46,433 --> 00:01:50,866
Lucien: [chuckles] ...Is it real?

24
00:01:50,866 --> 00:01:54,533
MC: Hum hum, of course it's real.

25
00:01:54,533 --> 00:01:59,133
MC: Lately, for some unknown reason, the real Nobi Rabbit has been appearing in Loveland City!

26
00:01:59,133 --> 00:02:03,833
MC: Now there’s already a wave of 'Nobi craze'. Everyone’s trying all kinds of ways to get her to appear by their side and play with her.

27
00:02:03,833 --> 00:02:13,500
Lucien: So, all the new merchandise added at home over the past few days, including that 'magical' cuddle claw machine, is meant to make Nobi show up faster?

28
00:02:13,500 --> 00:02:17,000
MC: Sort of. Gotta make an effort to raise the chance of being the lucky one, right...

29
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:21,166
Before I can finish my sentence, Lucien gently pinches my cheek.

30
00:02:21,166 --> 00:02:26,300
Lucien: I think my little one is already very lucky.

31
00:02:26,300 --> 00:02:32,200
Lucien: And you always share your luck with me so generously.

32
00:02:32,200 --> 00:02:41,900
Lucien: Whether it’s the RV trip, the island holiday… even a strand of blessing bracelets, or a fortune cookie.

33
00:02:41,900 --> 00:02:49,033
Lucien: You haven’t forgotten all of that, have you? Because then I would be heartbroken.

34
00:02:49,033 --> 00:02:56,366
Lucien’s voice is low and soft, as if coquettishly coaxing me, yet the tail end of his tone carries a firmness that leaves no room for doubt.

35
00:02:56,366 --> 00:03:02,700
Accompanied by his words, memories of those sweet and happy moments from the past surface in my mind.

36
00:03:02,700 --> 00:03:08,000
All those big and small moments of luck that had Lucien in them.

37
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:11,633
A smile rises on my face without me realizing it, and I lean against his shoulder.

38
00:03:11,633 --> 00:03:16,866
MC: Gee~ When you put it like that, I feel embarrassed.

39
00:03:16,866 --> 00:03:23,100
MC: It makes me seem like someone who’s already so lucky, yet still greedily wants more.

40
00:03:23,100 --> 00:03:30,033
Lucien: But your expression doesn't look 'embarrassed' at all.

41
00:03:30,033 --> 00:03:33,800
MC: Hm? Then what kind of expression do I have?

42
00:03:33,800 --> 00:03:37,400
Just as I lift my face, a soft kiss lands at the corner of my lips.

43
00:03:37,400 --> 00:03:46,466
Lucien: It’s a righteously bold, greedy expression, one that says you want to become the luckiest person in the world.

44
00:03:46,466 --> 00:03:51,533
I burst out laughing and reach out to hook my arm around Lucien’s neck.

45
00:03:51,533 --> 00:03:55,733
MC: Then, is it okay if I want to be a little greedier?

46
00:03:55,733 --> 00:04:01,033
Lucien: Sure. What do you want?

47
00:04:01,033 --> 00:04:04,133
MC: Of course, it is…

48
00:04:04,133 --> 00:04:09,666
I gently press down on his neck with my wrist, letting his breath blend once again with mine.

49
00:04:09,666 --> 00:04:15,933
MC: Lucien also has to become the luckiest person in the world together with me.

50
00:04:22,633 --> 00:04:29,100
Lucien: All right... how soon can you get here?

51
00:04:29,100 --> 00:04:34,133
Lucien: Please hurry as fast as possible, over here....

52
00:04:34,133 --> 00:04:42,600
Through the slightly ajar door, Lucien’s voice sounds fuzzy and distant, as if mingled with the drip-drop of water.

53
00:04:42,600 --> 00:04:49,166
Is it still raining? I frown, opening my eyes from the lingering daze of sleep, only to see a bright, cloudless sky outside the window.

54
00:04:49,166 --> 00:04:53,133
MC: Then the water sound just now was....

55
00:04:53,133 --> 00:04:56,666
Just as I’m puzzling over it, Lucien happens to push open the door. His eyes pause for a beat.

56
00:04:56,666 --> 00:05:00,000
Lucien: Did I wake you?

57
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:04,266
MC: No… were you on the phone just now?

58
00:05:04,266 --> 00:05:12,300
Lucien: Yes, there’s a bit of an issue with the drainage pipe on the balcony at home. I just contacted property management.

59
00:05:12,300 --> 00:05:15,700
MC: Huh?!

60
00:05:16,933 --> 00:05:21,066
Drip, drip...

61
00:05:21,066 --> 00:05:25,333
Gazing at the dripping mess strewn across the balcony, I feel as if my mood has also been soaked through by the muddy water.

62
00:05:25,333 --> 00:05:27,533
MC: How could this happen...

63
00:05:27,533 --> 00:05:32,933
MC: Just yesterday I said we have to become the luckiest people, and we already ran into something this unlucky today, sigh.

64
00:05:32,933 --> 00:05:37,400
Hearing my sigh, Lucien gently rubs my head.

65
00:05:37,400 --> 00:05:45,800
Lucien: Look on the bright side, at least it was discovered early. Otherwise, our living room floor would've been ruined too.

66
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:50,233
MC: That's true. Luckily, it’s not like what happened to me last time…

67
00:05:50,233 --> 00:05:54,066
I trail off mid-sentence and turn to look at Lucien. A knowing smile lifts the corners of his mouth.

68
00:05:54,066 --> 00:06:05,433
Lucien: Yeah. Now we've both experienced ‘The flooded Jinshan’.
[T/N: They were talking about what happened during the 2020 Valentine’s Day date (the one with cherry cg), when MC’s apartment got flooded and she ended up spending the night at Lucien’s place."The Flooded Jinshan" (水漫金山) alludes to a legendary scene from The Legend of the White Snake in which the White Snake floods Jinshan Temple to rescue her husband, Xu Xian. This phrase is often used to refer unfortunate occurrence of flooding]

69
00:06:05,433 --> 00:06:10,666
His gentle, joking tone melts away my gloom. I let out a sigh of relief and simply take his hand.

70
00:06:10,666 --> 00:06:17,666
MC: Then, in the spirit of 'courtesy demands reciprocity', how about coming over to my place as a guest while we wait for the property maintenance, Professor Xu?

71
00:06:17,666 --> 00:06:23,400
A bright gleam flashes in Lucien’s eyes. He gently squeezes my palm, his eyes curving into a smile.

72
00:06:23,400 --> 00:06:29,233
Lucien: Alright, I’ll trouble Miss Producer to take me in.

73
00:06:30,633 --> 00:06:33,033
As I begin excitedly planning how to properly host Lucien, I open my door—

74
00:06:33,033 --> 00:06:37,533
Suddenly, I feel something bump against my calf, and a crisp, chirpy voice chimes out from near my feet.

75
00:06:37,533 --> 00:06:40,366
??: Wow, your place is pretty big!

76
00:06:40,366 --> 00:06:44,300
I glance down. To my surprise, a Nobi rabbit has already bounced ahead of me into my home!

77
00:06:44,300 --> 00:06:48,566
MC: ?!

78
00:06:48,566 --> 00:06:53,166
My eyes widen as I stare in disbelief. Hearing my gasp, Nobi comes to a stop and lifts her chin at me.

79
00:06:53,166 --> 00:06:57,766
Nobi: Don’t you chat with me on your computer every day? How come you don't recognize me?

80
00:06:57,766 --> 00:07:02,400
MC: Of course I recognize you! Y-you're really Nobi?

81
00:07:02,400 --> 00:07:08,533
Nobi: Hmph! Who else in the whole world could possibly be this adorable besides me?

82
00:07:08,533 --> 00:07:14,166
Nobi: You two shouldn't just stand at the doorway. Come on in.

83
00:07:14,166 --> 00:07:19,533
After finishing her sentence, Nobi plops down onto my couch without a care in the world.

84
00:07:19,533 --> 00:07:26,533
Lucien watches the little bunny rolling around before him, letting a rare flicker of subtle expression surface on his face

85
00:07:26,533 --> 00:07:31,666
Yet before I can confirm it, he has already returned to his usual composed demeanor, giving me a helpless smile.

86
00:07:31,666 --> 00:07:37,833
Lucien: Looks like there’s a new guest besides me today.

87
00:07:39,166 --> 00:07:43,566
With that, he takes my hand and leads me over to Nobi.

88
00:07:43,566 --> 00:07:47,833
Lucien: Hello, Nobi Rabbit.

89
00:07:47,833 --> 00:07:53,666
Lucien: Can you tell me where you came from?

90
00:07:53,666 --> 00:07:58,566
Nobi: Um? I came from the cutest planet in the entire universe.

91
00:07:58,566 --> 00:08:06,900
Lucien: Then, by what means did you arrive here? Was it through spatial teleportation or energy conversion?

92
00:08:06,900 --> 00:08:12,333
Lucien’s gaze is filled with genuine curiosity and thirst for knowledge. Nobi puffs up her cheeks, seemingly a bit overwhelmed.

93
00:08:12,333 --> 00:08:16,966
Nobi: W-why do you humans like to ask strange questions?

94
00:08:16,966 --> 00:08:21,533
She firmly plants her hands on her hips and shakes her ears.

95
00:08:21,533 --> 00:08:27,466
Nobi: Anyway, the reason I appeared here is 'love'!

96
00:08:27,466 --> 00:08:33,566
Nobi: As long as there’s love, anything can be explained. That’s just how this world is!

97
00:08:33,566 --> 00:08:39,633
Because of Nobi’s righteously confident statement, the air goes quiet for a moment, then Lucien and I can’t help but chuckle at her answer.

98
00:08:39,633 --> 00:08:46,100
Lucien: Alright, that question just now really was a bit much for a little bunny.

99
00:08:46,100 --> 00:08:51,566
Lucien: After all, the world truly does become simpler because of love.

100
00:08:51,566 --> 00:08:57,033
Our eyes meet, and in silent unison, tender, indulgent smiles bloom on our faces. I scoot closer to Nobi’s side and give her a light poke.

101
00:08:57,033 --> 00:09:02,200
MC: Oh~ so does that mean it was the power of love between Lucien and me that drew you to appear here?

102
00:09:02,200 --> 00:09:05,366
Nobi: Yes, yes, exactly!

103
00:09:05,366 --> 00:09:10,633
Nobi: Professor Xu, you should learn from your girlfriend. She's much smarter and cuter than you!

104
00:09:10,633 --> 00:09:14,133
Lucien: ….

105
00:09:14,133 --> 00:09:20,033
Nobi and I tease in tandem, making him lift his brow slightly. He then bows down just a bit, as if earnestly seeking guidance.

106
00:09:20,033 --> 00:09:29,133
Lucien: Then, may I ask my two teachers what I can do to become as smart and as cute as my girlfriend?

107
00:09:29,133 --> 00:09:33,766
As if reclaiming her dignity, Nobi adjusts her glasses and nods with satisfaction.

108
00:09:33,766 --> 00:09:40,500
Nobi: That’s the very reason I came to you two~

109
00:09:40,500 --> 00:09:45,866
As she speaks, Nobi suddenly hops onto Lucien’s shoulder, leans in close to his ear, and whispers something softly.

110
00:09:45,866 --> 00:09:52,000
Lucien: [gasps softly] ...Really?

111
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:56,366
Nobi: Just try it and you'll see.

112
00:09:56,366 --> 00:10:00,800
Lucien nods thoughtfully, then leans down toward me.

113
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:06,566
Watching his face draw closer and closer, my heartbeat begins to race beyond my control.

114
00:10:06,566 --> 00:10:12,633
Yet Lucien merely extends his hand, guiding mine to his face, then slowly moving it upward.

115
00:10:12,633 --> 00:10:18,900
My fingertips glide from the warmth of his cheek, tangle through the fine strands of his hair, and finally come to rest on the fluffy crown of his head.

116
00:10:18,900 --> 00:10:26,466
The tactile sensations are magnified infinitely under his guidance, just like his innocent eyes that now occupy my whole vision.

117
00:10:26,466 --> 00:10:30,833
Lucien: …Am I cute?

118
00:10:30,833 --> 00:10:33,000
I blurt out almost reflexively:

119
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:38,300
MC: —So cute!!

120
00:10:41,866 --> 00:10:47,700
Just as I’m still basking in the lingering thrill of his adorable assault, Lucien’s phone begins to ring.

121
00:10:47,700 --> 00:10:55,200
Seeing that it's a call from property management, I pout my lips, can't help but nuzzle once more against Lucien’s fluffy hair, and only then do I longingly send him out the door.

122
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:59,900
Taking advantage of the moment while Lucien deals with property management, I quietly move closer to Nobi and ask in a whisper.

123
00:10:59,900 --> 00:11:03,600
MC: Nobi, do you have mind-reading powers? How do you know that I... am so susceptible to Lucien's tricks?

124
00:11:03,600 --> 00:11:08,300
Nobi: Hm? Didn’t you tell me all that yourself?

125
00:11:08,300 --> 00:11:14,166
Nobi hops onto my lap, her big eyes behind the lenses blinking at me.

126
00:11:14,166 --> 00:11:17,700
Nobi: You said the person you like most is Professor Xu, and that you have endless things to say to him every single day.

127
00:11:17,700 --> 00:11:24,466
Nobi: Although others see him as a serious and proper genius professor, you think the more a man is like that, the more suitable he is for...

128
00:11:24,466 --> 00:11:29,200
MC: Aaaah! STOP! Stop! I get it! Don’t go on!

129
00:11:29,200 --> 00:11:33,666
I didn’t expect that the real-life Nobi would actually remember everything from her time as a desktop pet!

130
00:11:33,666 --> 00:11:40,566
The moment I remember whispering all those unfiltered secrets to the little desktop pet, my face burns hot in an instant.

131
00:11:40,566 --> 00:11:46,066
I quickly change the subject to stop her from rambling on.

132
00:11:46,066 --> 00:11:50,933
MC: Th-then how did you make Lucien willing to do this?

133
00:11:50,933 --> 00:11:54,933
Nobi: Hahaha, it’s a secret spell I whispered to him.

134
00:11:54,933 --> 00:12:00,433
Nobi smugly shakes her ears and shoots me a triumphant glance.

135
00:12:00,433 --> 00:12:05,600
Nobi: Anyway, today he’s definitely going to fulfill all your demands.

136
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:10,400
All of my demands.

137
00:12:10,400 --> 00:12:15,466
Those four words brush across the bottom of my heart like tiny feathers, leaving a faint, ticklish sensation.

138
00:12:15,466 --> 00:12:19,500
Just as I'm about to ask something else, the door suddenly opens, and Lucien shuffles in, holding a delivery box in his arms.

139
00:12:19,500 --> 00:12:23,066
A little surprised, I hurry over to lend him a hand.

140
00:12:23,066 --> 00:12:28,833
MC: So fast? Is the pipe already fixed?

141
00:12:28,833 --> 00:12:32,133
He shakes his head and lets out a troubled sigh.

142
00:12:32,133 --> 00:12:39,466
Lucien: The repairs can't be done today. The maintenance worker said it's a bit complicated and will probably need to inspect it together with the unit upstairs tomorrow.

143
00:12:39,466 --> 00:12:43,800
Lucien: Oh, and this is the package that was at your door.

144
00:12:43,800 --> 00:12:47,100
I freeze for a moment before I can fully process the meaning behind those two sentences.

145
00:12:47,100 --> 00:12:50,666
MC: So... you're staying at my place today?

146
00:12:50,666 --> 00:12:54,933
Lucien: Can't I?

147
00:12:54,933 --> 00:13:02,000
I'm just about to nod along with what he says when Nobi's words just now sweep through my mind again, and my gaze involuntarily drifts to the delivery box in his hands.

148
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:06,633
Of course, I know what's inside the delivery box. If all these things could appear on Lucien...

149
00:13:06,633 --> 00:13:12,133
I blink, and then a huge smile spreads across my face.

150
00:13:12,133 --> 00:13:20,600
MC: Of course you can! But you need to be good and do as I say, abide by the principle 'guest adapts to host’s arrangements'.

151
00:13:20,600 --> 00:13:25,333
I take the delivery box from his hands and tear it open, then pull out a set of soft, plush pajamas with adorable bunny ears... Nobi Rabbit-themed sleepwear!

152
00:13:25,333 --> 00:13:31,433
Wiggling the pajamas at Lucien, I smile at him with eyes curved like crescent moons.

153
00:13:31,433 --> 00:13:38,200
MC: If you’re staying at my home, then you’ve got to wear the pajamas from my place~

154
00:13:38,200 --> 00:13:43,533
Lucien casts a glance at that fluffy set and smiles faintly.

155
00:13:43,533 --> 00:13:50,666
Lucien: Whatever your arrangements, I am at your command.

156
00:13:51,833 --> 00:13:59,100
It’s not often that the weather is this sunny and clear, so I pull Lucien along, bring out the lounge chair and tea table, and get ready to comfortably enjoy a ‘stay-at-home sunbath’.

157
00:13:59,100 --> 00:14:04,200
I enthusiastically lay out the cushions and arrange the drinks and snacks, but then discover there’s still a pillow missing from the rattan chair.

158
00:14:04,200 --> 00:14:07,200
MC: Ah, I almost forgot!

159
00:14:07,200 --> 00:14:12,600
I rise to my feet, clap my hands, then turn with a smile to tell Lucien and Nobi, "Wait here for a bit!"—before briskly darting back to the bedroom to fetch the pillow.

160
00:14:14,033 --> 00:14:19,633
MC: Anyway, there's still one day off tomorrow. How about taking Nobi out for some fun with Lucien?

161
00:14:19,633 --> 00:14:26,400
MC: Where to go though... that newly opened ball pit park sounds like a good idea...

162
00:14:26,400 --> 00:14:29,833
As I mull it over, I pick up the pillow and walk out of the bedroom.

163
00:14:31,133 --> 00:14:34,100
A richly scented summer breeze flutters through the balcony curtains, and the first thing that meets my eyes is a pair of fluffy, gently swaying—

164
00:14:34,100 --> 00:14:35,466
—bunny ears.

165
00:14:35,466 --> 00:14:38,500
Lucien wears the bunny pajamas, surrounded by a circle of Nobi merchandise and greenery, even the air is infused with a noisy warmth.

166
00:14:38,500 --> 00:14:41,166
Yet amid all the blooming abundance, the rowdiest of all is still Nobi Rabbit, spinning noisily around Lucien.

167
00:14:41,166 --> 00:14:44,233
Everything under the sunshine softens my heart. I lighten my footsteps, quietly pulling out my phone to capture this scene.

168
00:14:44,233 --> 00:14:46,466
Nobi: So then, why do you think this is the cutest thing about MC?

169
00:14:46,466 --> 00:14:48,700
...Are they talking about me? I instantly perk up my ears as I try to eavesdrop on Lucien’s answer.

170
00:14:48,700 --> 00:14:50,933
With his back to me in the camera frame, Lucien lets out a deliberately profound "Hmm."

171
00:14:50,933 --> 00:14:58,100
Lucien: For that, I should likely begin with the activity levels of dopamine neurons in the medial prefrontal cortex.

172
00:14:58,100 --> 00:15:04,866
Lucien: When I make eye contact or talk with her, there are significant fluctuations in the secretion of oxytocin and serotonin.

173
00:15:04,866 --> 00:15:14,600
Lucien: This kind of neurochemical reaction forms memories through the hippocampus, gradually establishing a conditioned reflex in my subconscious where "MC = cute"....

174
00:15:14,600 --> 00:15:15,866
Nobi: Ack!

175
00:15:15,866 --> 00:15:18,333
Nobi lets out a cry and clutches her head as if she's dizzy, plopping down onto the pillow with a wobbly flop.

176
00:15:18,333 --> 00:15:20,033
Nobi: You're truly way too un-cute!

177
00:15:20,033 --> 00:15:21,500
MC: Pffft-HAHAHA!

178
00:15:21,500 --> 00:15:23,566
Unable to hold back, I finally burst out laughing. Lucien turns his head at the sound.

179
00:15:23,566 --> 00:15:26,333
The bunny ears tremble in the breeze, and the soft, plush material makes him look several times softer and gentler than usual.

180
00:15:26,333 --> 00:15:33,133
Beneath the purple bow, his long, narrow eyes brim with helplessness, yet the smile at the corner of his lips is full of sly mischief.

181
00:15:33,133 --> 00:15:42,066
Hmph, he doesn’t look like a bunny at all. He’s clearly a little fox in bunny’s clothing.

182
00:15:43,400 --> 00:15:49,400
I can’t help but reach out and pinch his 'bunny ears'.

183
00:15:49,400 --> 00:15:57,600
Lucien doesn’t dodge my 'troublemaking'. Instead, he squints his eyes, leans in, and nuzzles against my palm.

184
00:15:57,600 --> 00:16:03,833
Lucien: What should I do, Teacher MC? I’ve been called un-cute again.

185
00:16:03,833 --> 00:16:07,133
MC: Well then, Little Student Lulu needs to study hard and follow Nobi’s and my guidance

186
00:16:07,133 --> 00:16:15,766
Lucien: Little Student Lulu? [chuckles] Is that nickname also part of becoming cute?

187
00:16:15,766 --> 00:16:18,300
MC: That's right, and also...

188
00:16:18,300 --> 00:16:22,433
I excitedly take out one little accessory after another from the delivery box and clip them onto Lucien’s hair.

189
00:16:22,433 --> 00:16:27,000
While I’m at it, I open my phone's camera and select the most over-the-top, cutesy filter.

190
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:31,933
Seeing Lucien turn into a 'big-eyed moe boy' on screen, a wave of mischievous pride wells up in my heart.

191
00:16:31,933 --> 00:16:37,366
MC: Mmhmm, this Little Student Lulu is definitely cute!

192
00:16:37,366 --> 00:16:43,066
Lucien: …..

193
00:16:43,066 --> 00:16:48,600
Lucien reaches up to touch the newly added pink hair accessory on his head, then raises an eyebrow in understanding.

194
00:16:48,600 --> 00:16:53,633
Lucien: I see. I’ve learned it now.

195
00:16:53,633 --> 00:17:05,600
Lucien: As a good student, I'll naturally follow the teacher's guidance. But as a good teacher, shouldn't MC also lead by example?

196
00:17:05,600 --> 00:17:08,800
MC: Lead by example how?

197
00:17:08,800 --> 00:17:11,700
Lucien: For example...

198
00:17:11,700 --> 00:17:17,100
Lucien leans in and sweeps me into his arms in one smooth, irresistible motion.

199
00:17:17,100 --> 00:17:23,500
The delicate fragrance of gardenias still lingers in his sleeves. A scent that belongs to Lucien alone.

200
00:17:23,500 --> 00:17:29,433
Then he takes my phone with one hand, and with the other, he plucks the spare hair accessories from my grasp, mimicking me as he clips them into my hair.

201
00:17:29,433 --> 00:17:34,233
Looking at the two of us on screen, wearing the same hair clips and surrounded by pink bubbles and flowers, it feels as if bubbles and blossoms are rising and blooming in my heart too.

202
00:17:34,233 --> 00:17:39,900
Lucien’s satisfied chuckle sounds softly by my ear.

203
00:17:39,900 --> 00:17:49,166
Lucien: So next, how should I face the camera in a 'cute' way? Little Teacher MC, can you teach me?

204
00:17:53,066 --> 00:17:59,300
With Nobi’s guidance, we not only play lots of fun little games but also boldly try filming all sorts of childish little videos.

205
00:17:59,300 --> 00:18:06,466
Just as Nobi promised at the beginning, Lucien always indulges and goes along with my antics.

206
00:18:08,000 --> 00:18:12,800
As night gradually descends, Nobi suddenly jumps onto the center of the coffee table and solemnly adjusts her round glasses.

207
00:18:12,800 --> 00:18:17,166
Nobi: Alright, my dear students, I’m leaving now.

208
00:18:17,166 --> 00:18:20,900
MC: So sudden? I was hoping to go to the ball pit park with you tomorrow!

209
00:18:20,900 --> 00:18:26,733
Hearing my plea to stay, Nobi’s figure wavers slightly, her expression clearly falters, but she quickly pretends to be serious and shakes her ears.

210
00:18:26,733 --> 00:18:32,800
Nobi: It’s no surprise you can’t bear to see me go. After all, I’m everyone's favorite little bunny!

211
00:18:32,800 --> 00:18:41,233
Nobi: But as the universe’s cutest Nobi Rabbit, I must keep helping more people become even more adorable!

212
00:18:41,233 --> 00:18:45,833
After saying that, Nobi immediately pounces into my arms, affectionately rubbing against my cheek. She then hops onto Lucien's shoulder, cups his cheek, and rubs against it too.

213
00:18:45,833 --> 00:18:50,300
Lucien and I look at each other and smile, then tacitly reach out to gently rub her fluffy cheeks.

214
00:18:50,300 --> 00:18:54,833
MC: Thank youuu, Teacher Nobi~

215
00:18:54,833 --> 00:19:02,866
Lucien: I will also remember your teachings. I promise I’ll continue becoming cuter from now on.

216
00:19:02,866 --> 00:19:07,266
After a round of ‘cuddly’ goodbyes, Nobi finally darts over to the windowsill and waves her tiny paw at us.

217
00:19:07,266 --> 00:19:11,933
Nobi: Bye-bye the cutest couple in Loveland City second only to me!

218
00:19:13,433 --> 00:19:19,466
Only after watching Nobi disappear into the night do I reluctantly withdraw my gaze and turn to look at the room filled with Nobi merchandise.

219
00:19:19,466 --> 00:19:23,400
MC: It’s getting late. Shall we tidy up the balcony together?

220
00:19:23,400 --> 00:19:27,066
Lucien says "Mm" in response. He picks up the pillow from the lounge chair and suddenly speaks.

221
00:19:27,066 --> 00:19:32,866
Lucien: Have you told Nobi a lot about me?

222
00:19:32,866 --> 00:19:37,400
MC: Huh? How did you know?

223
00:19:37,400 --> 00:19:44,800
Lucien: From what I observed today, there was a certain tacit understanding between you and her in your 'guidance' toward me.

224
00:19:44,800 --> 00:19:48,900
MC: ….!

225
00:19:48,900 --> 00:19:53,300
My face turns red all at once, and I stammer as I wave my hand.

226
00:19:53,300 --> 00:19:58,933
MC: Uh, I just chatted with her about some girl talk, that’s all.

227
00:19:58,933 --> 00:20:04,166
Lucien props his chin on a pillow, a faintly mischievous tone lacing his voice.

228
00:20:04,166 --> 00:20:15,633
Lucien: So you have told her a lot of secrets about me. Sigh... Looks like I’m no longer your first choice for sharing secrets.

229
00:20:15,633 --> 00:20:18,233
MC: That's not true at all!

230
00:20:18,233 --> 00:20:21,500
I hastily deny it, yet have no idea how to explain.

231
00:20:21,500 --> 00:20:24,966
MC: It’s just… uh…

232
00:20:24,966 --> 00:20:31,333
MC: Sometimes people fantasize about things that are unlikely to happen. But normally, who would have the nerve to actually ask the other person to do such things?

233
00:20:31,333 --> 00:20:35,866
MC: I’m just casually chatting with Nobi…

234
00:20:35,866 --> 00:20:39,600
Lucien takes a step forward, drawing out his ending tone as the smile at the corners of his mouth deepens.

235
00:20:39,600 --> 00:20:50,766
Lucien: So today, you had me wear a bunny onesie, act cute to you, play childish games, and film adorable videos...

236
00:20:50,766 --> 00:20:57,933
Lucien: Were all these lessons your 'fantasies coming true', MC?

237
00:20:57,933 --> 00:21:02,433
As he lists off today's antics one by one, my face grows even hotter, nearly overwhelmed with guilt for my unrestrained indulgence.

238
00:21:02,433 --> 00:21:06,900
Lucien gently pinches my flushed cheek.

239
00:21:06,900 --> 00:21:16,300
Lucien: Silly, there's no need to feel embarrassed. I genuinely like this feeling of ‘psychological regression’ today.

240
00:21:16,300 --> 00:21:20,933
MC: Psychological regression?

241
00:21:20,933 --> 00:21:31,633
Lucien: When someone is in a highly trusting and secure relationship, the brain subconsciously chooses to return to a relatively simpler and more relaxed state.

242
00:21:31,633 --> 00:21:39,000
Lucien: It’s similar to the carefree feeling during childhood.

243
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:49,800
Lucien: Sometimes, being in a state of regression actually helps us express our needs and authentic inner thoughts more clearly.

244
00:21:49,800 --> 00:21:53,333
I blink and take the pillow Lucien hands to me.

245
00:21:53,333 --> 00:22:01,600
MC: So… do you also have moments when you really want to see that side of the other person, but feel too embarrassed to say it because it seems childish?

246
00:22:01,600 --> 00:22:07,866
Lucien pauses at my words, as if he earnestly thinks it over for a moment before smiling and nodding.

247
00:22:07,866 --> 00:22:15,266
Lucien: You mean willful thoughts like yours? Yeah, I do have those.

248
00:22:15,266 --> 00:22:19,133
MC: Eh? Like what?

249
00:22:20,933 --> 00:22:22,666
Lucien smiles without answering and simply reaches out to gently take hold of my wrist.

250
00:22:22,666 --> 00:22:24,633
In the next second, the world spins before my eyes, and the ground beneath me suddenly softens—

251
00:22:24,633 --> 00:22:27,366
Swirling colorful lights fill my vision as my whole body unexpectedly sinks into an ocean of pillowy soft balls!

252
00:22:27,366 --> 00:22:30,300
I look up in surprise at Lucien, who’s fallen into the ball pit alongside me, and he gives me an innocent smile.

253
00:22:30,300 --> 00:22:35,933
Lucien: When I heard those childish requests of yours, I was indeed a bit surprised.

254
00:22:35,933 --> 00:22:37,966
MC: Are you surprised at my childishness?

255
00:22:37,966 --> 00:22:51,600
Lucien: No. Surprised that I hadn’t done enough, that I should’ve enabled my little lady to 'regress' by my side without holding anything back… much, much earlier.

256
00:22:51,600 --> 00:22:55,966
He shifts his posture slightly, letting himself sink even deeper into the soft sea of plastic orbs.

257
00:22:55,966 --> 00:23:00,400
Colorful spheres tumble around us with a soft rumble as his gaze settles tenderly on my face.

258
00:23:00,400 --> 00:23:06,700
Lucien: Letting myself be childish with you to our hearts' content like this... I really like it.

259
00:23:06,700 --> 00:23:11,266
His voice whispers softly in my ear. It becomes the warmest comfort, filling my heart with a feather-light happiness.

260
00:23:11,266 --> 00:23:14,333
MC: So, what exactly did Nobi teach you that made you so willing to grant my every wish today?

261
00:23:14,333 --> 00:23:17,900
Lucien: Actually, it's only two words.

262
00:23:17,900 --> 00:23:21,200
I blink, looking at him in confusion, while Lucien nods seriously and pulls my hand onto his soft, fluffy hair.

263
00:23:21,200 --> 00:23:23,833
Lucien: Tactile feel.

264
00:23:23,833 --> 00:23:26,000
MC: Tactile feel?

265
00:23:26,000 --> 00:23:30,166
His voice is soft, like a light feather falling into my heart.

266
00:23:30,166 --> 00:23:39,833
Lucien: Nobi says that as long as you let your hand touch something soft, your heart will grow just as soft, too.

267
00:23:39,833 --> 00:23:45,400
His hair is delicate, soft, and fluffy. The warm sensation travels through my palm, and just like he said, my heart softly melts all at once.

268
00:23:45,400 --> 00:23:50,933
MC: I do admit, Professor Xu feels especially good to the touch today.

269
00:23:50,933 --> 00:23:55,200
Lucien: Is it just the way I feel that’s good?

270
00:23:55,200 --> 00:24:01,466
Lucien: I still want to hear you affirm my cuteness a little more.

271
00:24:01,466 --> 00:24:08,466
My heartbeat is stirred by his words and tender gaze. Without a second thought, I lean in and kiss him.

272
00:24:08,466 --> 00:24:13,733
MC: Everything about Lucien is incredibly cute

273
00:24:13,733 --> 00:24:19,833
In his embrace, my eyes crinkle into a smile. My fingers twirl strands of his hair round and round, and my heart, too, grows soft like a floating bubble.

274
00:24:21,533 --> 00:24:24,366
MC: By the way, what about me?

275
00:24:24,366 --> 00:24:31,133
MC: What do you think is the cutest thing about me? You’re not allowed to fool me with scientific reasoning like you did with Nobi earlier!

276
00:24:31,133 --> 00:24:37,066
MC: You have to say it one by one. Be specific.

277
00:24:37,066 --> 00:24:43,333
Lucien is slightly taken aback upon hearing this, then gives a helpless smile. His hands tenderly cradle my cheeks, his warm fingertips slowly tracing along my features.

278
00:24:43,333 --> 00:24:48,366
His fingers glide over the space between my brows, then gently rub my earlobe.

279
00:24:48,366 --> 00:25:01,333
Lucien: If… I had to choose the cutest part of you, then it would probably be your brows and eyes, your cheeks, the tip of your nose...

280
00:25:01,333 --> 00:25:07,433
His voice flows as softly as the night. With every word he speaks, a gentle yet solemn kiss falls upon my face.

281
00:25:07,433 --> 00:25:12,633
Moved by his earnest, tenderly lingering gesture, I can’t help but wrap my arms around his neck.

282
00:25:12,633 --> 00:25:17,766
MC: Oh~ Then which one is the cutest of all?

283
00:25:17,766 --> 00:25:21,166
Lucien: It's here.

284
00:25:21,166 --> 00:25:26,366
He pulls back slightly, gazing at me with a tender and wholly focused gaze.

285
00:25:26,366 --> 00:25:36,700
Lucien: The cutest of all… is your eyes that are forever overflowing with love.

286
00:25:36,700 --> 00:25:43,466
I'm just going to drop the translation of the moments here. This guy is too cute lol~ Also, there's one phone call [Couple Desktop Pets] from this card that I want to share after this.

287
00:25:43,466 --> 00:25:50,100
Lucien: It’s rare for you to call me right while you're at work. Is there something up?

288
00:25:50,100 --> 00:25:54,100
MC: Ahem, Lucien, are you free to help me record a few lines right now?

289
00:25:54,100 --> 00:26:01,033
Lucien: Hm? I guess I'm free... Is this for your new show production?

290
00:26:01,033 --> 00:26:06,433
MC: No, it's not that. Nobi has just released a limited-edition Children's Day desktop pet.

291
00:26:06,433 --> 00:26:11,500
MC: Not only can you customize desktop pets with couple avatars, but you can also record voice lines!

292
00:26:11,500 --> 00:26:19,400
Lucien: I see. So, what kind of lines would you like me to record?

293
00:26:19,400 --> 00:26:24,833
MC: Just some simple ones like "Hello~", "Goodbye", or "Do your best today too" and such.

294
00:26:24,833 --> 00:26:31,266
MC: That way, I’ll have a mini Lucien watching over me while I work~

295
00:26:31,266 --> 00:26:38,900
Lucien: So that’s what Miss Producer was planning all along.

296
00:26:38,900 --> 00:26:45,133
MC: Hehe, so… would you be willing to play along?

297
00:26:45,133 --> 00:26:56,266
Lucien: Of course I’m willing. But since it’s a couple-edition desktop pet… shouldn’t I have a "Mini Producer" on my desktop as well?

298
00:26:56,266 --> 00:27:00,666
MC: Eh? You want to keep a mini version of me too?

299
00:27:00,666 --> 00:27:04,866
Lucien: Can't I?

300
00:27:04,866 --> 00:27:10,900
MC: I mean, you can...... but how are you planning to design my desktop pet avatar?

301
00:27:10,900 --> 00:27:20,366
Lucien: For example, endlessly curious, enjoys experiencing all kinds of life’s little joys, and always brings me small, delightful surprises...

302
00:27:20,366 --> 00:27:30,700
Lucien: And when she eats something delicious, she gives a silly little smile, and when she’s asleep, she instinctively burrows into my chest...

303
00:27:30,700 --> 00:27:36,433
MC: W-wait a second. Lucien, isn’t your impression of me a little too specific?

304
00:27:36,433 --> 00:27:45,433
Lucien: Is it? I haven’t even mentioned the more specific and cuter details yet.

305
00:27:45,433 --> 00:27:53,300
MC: Ahem... Okay, let’s not talk about that for now. So, do you have any lines you'd like me to record for your desktop pet?

306
00:27:53,300 --> 00:27:57,866
Lucien: I only need you to record one sentence.

307
00:27:57,866 --> 00:28:02,733
MC: Which sentence?

308
00:28:02,733 --> 00:28:09,200
Lucien: Just the simplest words—meant just for me—

309
00:28:09,200 --> 00:28:13,966
Lucien:"Love you."